  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "MK",
    "text": "This is the reunion of the Birkenau boys, the group that experienced the Mengele selection on July 4, 1944. We met in Givat Haim at Beit Terezin in Israel in 1990, on the anniversary of our liberation on June 5-- on May 5. This picture was taken on the occasion of my daughter's wedding in Vermont, in September 1995. From left to right, it is myself, Michael Kraus. Next to me is my wife, Ilana Kraus. Next to her in the middle is Dana, the bride, and to the far right, in the first row, is my other, younger daughter, Tamara. Behind her is her boyfriend, Dan, and behind Dana is her husband, Tom Forster. This is my daughter's, Dana, wedding. Next to her is her husband, Tom Forster, and in the background is Rabbi Kudan, who officiated the service. And my head, with the kippah, is in the foreground.",
